# Crypto Market Data Analysis

This project collects cryptocurrency market data using the CoinGecko API and prepares it for analysis.

## Project Overview

The goal of this project is to demonstrate a basic data analysis pipeline:

API → Python → Data Cleaning → Feature Engineering → Dataset Export

The dataset is later used for analysis and visualization.

## Tools Used

- Python
- Pandas
- Requests
- Matplotlib
- Seaborn
- CoinGecko API

## Data Collection

Cryptocurrency market data is collected from the CoinGecko API using Python.

The raw JSON response is converted into a pandas DataFrame and cleaned to keep only relevant analytical columns.

## Feature Engineering

Additional analytical columns were created:

- price_distance_from_ath
- price_distance_from_atl
- volatility_estimate

These metrics help analyze market volatility and price positioning.

## Dataset

The cleaned dataset is exported as:

data/crypto_market_data.csv

This dataset contains key cryptocurrency metrics such as:

- current price
- market capitalization
- trading volume
- price change (24h)
- circulating supply
- all-time highs and lows

## Future Work

Next steps include:

- SQL-based analysis
- building a Power BI dashboard
- deeper exploratory data analysis (EDA)
